    ## Conclusion

    - After a page refresh, NVDA always announces the webpage's `<title>`, followed by <q>Document</q>, followed by the page's content
    - If there's no content, NVDA announces <q>Blank</q>
    - Content can be hidden from screenreaders using the `aria-hidden="true"` attribute

